have a rubber ducky?

00:40:38.060 --> 00:40:39.360
&gt;&gt; No.

00:40:39.360 --> 00:40:41.320
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald: She
doesn't actually carry this

00:40:41.320 --> 00:40:44.860
in her purse, but I learned
when I was researching,

00:40:44.860 --> 00:40:48.660
the queen actually has a rubber
ducky in the royal bathroom

00:40:48.660 --> 00:40:53.790
and her rubber ducky wears
a crown, isn't that crazy?

00:40:53.790 --> 00:40:57.850
Okay, now this one's really
crazy, do you think the Queen

00:40:57.850 --> 00:41:05.480
of England would have in her
purse, a spark plug from a car?

00:41:05.480 --> 00:41:06.780
&gt;&gt; No.

00:41:06.780 --> 00:41:10.630
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald: No, she
probably doesn't carry her own

00:41:10.630 --> 00:41:13.730
but I learned, the queen even
though she's 90 years old,

00:41:13.730 --> 00:41:17.000
she knows how to change
a spark plug in the car,

00:41:17.000 --> 00:41:20.540
so if the royal palace car
breaks down, the queen can get

00:41:20.540 --> 00:41:22.830
out and change the spark plug.

00:41:22.830 --> 00:41:25.330
Pretty cool huh?

00:41:25.330 --> 00:41:28.600
And, last of all, do you
think the queen would have

00:41:28.600 --> 00:41:33.100
in her purse, a lucky charm?

00:41:33.100 --> 00:41:34.400
&gt;&gt; Yes.

00:41:34.400 --> 00:41:35.700
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald:
You guys are good.

00:41:35.700 --> 00:41:37.000
How'd you know that.

00:41:37.000 --> 00:41:40.370
I thought no way would the
queen carry a lucky charm,

00:41:40.370 --> 00:41:41.670
but she does.

00:41:41.670 --> 00:41:42.990
She always has a lucky charm.

00:41:42.990 --> 00:41:48.060
However, I couldn't find
out what her lucky charm is,

00:41:48.060 --> 00:41:51.900
so if you ever get to meet the
Queen of England, please ask her

00:41:51.900 --> 00:41:56.480
for me what is your lucky
charm so we can find out.

00:41:56.480 --> 00:42:01.740
Okay, do you, does anybody
have a question you wanted

00:42:01.740 --> 00:42:04.270
to ask today before
it's time to go?

00:42:04.270 --> 00:42:05.570
Yeah?

00:42:05.570 --> 00:42:10.240
&gt;&gt; Will you make anymore,
will you make anymore, books,

00:42:10.240 --> 00:42:13.270
different books other
than Judy Moody?

00:42:13.270 --> 00:42:14.570
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald: Yes,

00:42:14.570 --> 00:42:19.230
so the question is will I make
anymore different books other

00:42:19.230 --> 00:42:20.830
than Judy Moody.

00:42:20.830 --> 00:42:24.330
I've actually been working on
a new book for about 2 years

00:42:24.330 --> 00:42:27.510
so far that's not
about Judy Moody.

00:42:27.510 --> 00:42:30.530
And, this book is so different
because it's a fantasy,

00:42:30.530 --> 00:42:34.700
so it's totally just made
up in my imagination,

00:42:34.700 --> 00:42:38.890
but maybe someday
I'll finish it.

00:42:38.890 --> 00:42:41.260
&gt;&gt; Will you ever like
have a clothing line

00:42:41.260 --> 00:42:44.340
with like Judy Moody, like
across like a hoodie or a shirt?

00:42:44.340 --> 00:42:46.760
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald: Ooh,
I'm so glad you said

00:42:46.760 --> 00:42:49.510
that since my publisher's
here today.

00:42:49.510 --> 00:42:53.360
[ Laughter ]

00:42:53.360 --> 00:42:57.230
&gt;&gt; We would love to do that
someday, but you can also go

00:42:57.230 --> 00:43:01.270
to the Judy Moody website
and you can print out the

00:43:01.270 --> 00:43:04.320
"I Ate a Shark" thing if you
want to make your own shirt,

00:43:04.320 --> 00:43:07.150
so that's pretty cool too.

00:43:09.170 --> 00:43:13.970
&gt;&gt; What I would like to
know is, how old are you?

00:43:13.970 --> 00:43:15.920
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald: How old am I?

00:43:15.920 --> 00:43:20.330
Oh boy, okay, I am,
let's see, I usually try

00:43:20.330 --> 00:43:23.090
to make it a math problem
so you can figure out.

00:43:23.090 --> 00:43:29.030
Okay, so my first book came
out when I was 30 years old

00:43:29.030 --> 00:43:34.510
and I've been writing books
for 30, almost 30 years.

00:43:34.510 --> 00:43:40.070
[ Multiple Speakers ]

00:43:40.070 --> 00:43:43.750
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald:
That's right, I'm 59, 58,

00:43:43.750 --> 00:43:47.630
59 or 60, one of those.

00:43:47.630 --> 00:43:52.370
I'm almost, I'm 59,
I'm almost 60.

00:43:52.370 --> 00:43:55.510
Next year I'll be 60 years old.

00:43:55.510 --> 00:43:58.080
[ Inaudible ]

00:43:58.080 --> 00:44:01.300
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald: Oh, thanks
you guys, keep saying that.

00:44:01.300 --> 00:44:05.350
Did everybody get that?

00:44:05.350 --> 00:44:06.650
Go ahead.

00:44:06.650 --> 00:44:08.220
&gt;&gt; How long have you been
doing Judy Moody books?

00:44:08.220 --> 00:44:09.520
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald: Okay,

00:44:09.520 --> 00:44:12.950
how long have I been
writing Judy Moody books?

00:44:12.950 --> 00:44:16.090
Well, long enough that kids
who are in college now,

00:44:16.090 --> 00:44:18.100
read Judy Moody when
they were young,

00:44:18.100 --> 00:44:23.350
so the first Judy Moody
book came out in the 2000,

00:44:23.350 --> 00:44:25.640
so for about 18 years.

00:44:25.640 --> 00:44:28.330
So, actually a little
more because I had

00:44:28.330 --> 00:44:30.750
to write the Judy
Moody book for a couple

00:44:30.750 --> 00:44:34.800
of years before it came out,
so probably about 20 years

00:44:34.800 --> 00:44:39.260
with Judy and Stink, so
they're like my family, right?

00:44:39.260 --> 00:44:43.170
Oh, sorry, no go ahead, sorry.

00:44:43.170 --> 00:44:46.790
&gt;&gt; Can we publish books
online, the Judy Moody books?

00:44:46.790 --> 00:44:48.090
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald:
Can you publish them?

00:44:48.090 --> 00:44:49.390
&gt;&gt; Like buy them.

00:44:49.390 --> 00:44:53.090
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald: Oh yeah,
you can buy them online, yeah.

00:44:53.090 --> 00:44:55.150
You can publish your own books.

00:44:55.150 --> 00:44:59.720
&gt;&gt; Have you met any of
the actors in the movie?

00:44:59.720 --> 00:45:02.950
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald: Oh
yeah, so we were so lucky.

00:45:02.950 --> 00:45:05.470
My husband and I
got to go on the set

00:45:05.470 --> 00:45:08.350
for 3 months while
they filmed the movie.

00:45:08.350 --> 00:45:11.650
Most writers don't usually
go be part of the movie,

00:45:11.650 --> 00:45:13.550
so I was really, really lucky.

00:45:13.550 --> 00:45:14.960
So, we met all the actors.

00:45:14.960 --> 00:45:18.510
The girl who played Judy Moody
was 11 years old and she was

00:45:18.510 --> 00:45:22.040
from Australia and she
had red hair that was kind

00:45:22.040 --> 00:45:23.740
of messy like Judy Moody.

00:45:23.740 --> 00:45:25.210
Well, she came from Australia,

00:45:25.210 --> 00:45:28.270
and in Australia they
have a different accent

00:45:28.270 --> 00:45:32.320
than we have here, so she had
to come a couple of months early

00:45:32.320 --> 00:45:34.360
and she had to get
a dialect coach,

00:45:34.360 --> 00:45:37.730
a person who could help
her to learn to speak

00:45:37.730 --> 00:45:39.880
with an American accent.

00:45:39.880 --> 00:45:43.500
And, then by the time we started
the movie, she was really good

00:45:43.500 --> 00:45:47.050
at speaking like an
American would sound.

00:45:47.050 --> 00:45:50.790
So, yeah, so we got to meet
all of the actors, all the,

00:45:50.790 --> 00:45:53.670
all the kids who played parts.

00:45:53.670 --> 00:45:57.770
Do you guys know who Urkel is?

00:45:57.770 --> 00:46:00.800
I don't, you know Steve Urkel?

00:46:00.800 --> 00:46:04.830
Steve Urkel, so he plays,

00:46:04.830 --> 00:46:08.700
Judy has the most wonderful 3rd
grade teacher ever, Mr. Todd

00:46:08.700 --> 00:46:11.610
and Urkel, his name
is Jaleel White,

00:46:11.610 --> 00:46:14.030
plays Mr. Todd in the movie.

00:46:14.030 --> 00:46:17.570
I know, see, pretty cool.

00:46:17.570 --> 00:46:20.480
Yeah, so, you've got to go and
watch it again and look for him.

00:46:20.480 --> 00:46:24.580
Yeah, exactly.

00:46:24.580 --> 00:46:25.880
Anybody else?

00:46:25.880 --> 00:46:29.350
&gt;&gt; Any questions?

00:46:29.350 --> 00:46:30.650
&gt;&gt; Megan McDonald: Okay.

00:46:30.650 --> 00:46:31.950
I think we're done.

00:46:31.950 --> 00:46:34.590
Thank you all so much
for coming to the Library

00:46:34.590 --> 00:46:37.100
of Congress today
to hear stories.

